<TITLE> Khaleda release imminent:Siddiqui </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 11 (bdnews24.com)  Former prime minister and BNP chief Khaleda Zia is going to be released on bail soon, after spending a year in detention, deputy inspector general of prisons Major Shamsul Haider Siddiqui said Thursday. "We hope Khaleda Zia will be released by 11:30 am. We have finished going through all the documents relating to her bail," Siddiqui told bdnews24.com. The former prime minister was preparing to leave the prison, the prisons official said. The jail authorities Wednesday received the documents relating to Khaleda Zia's bail. "The authorities received the documents at 6:45 pm, and she will be freed anytime tomorrow (Thursday)," Siddiqui said Wednesday night. Bail bonds for former prime minister Khaleda Zia were submitted by lawyers earlier Wednesday to four separate courts handling the GATCO, Niko, Zia Orphanage Trust and Barapukuria cases. Khaleda's lawyer Advocate Sanaullah Miah had earlier told bdnews24.com that the bail bonds of the four graft cases against were submitted and accepted by the courts. "The courts have informed us that all the papers relating to the bail bonds have been sent to the jail authorities." He had expressed the hope that the BNP chief would be freed Wednesday. Khaleda and her son Arafat Rahman Coco were arrested on Sept 3 last year in GATCO graft case. Later, three more graft cases were filed against her. She secured bail in all the cases. bdnews24.com/sm/ehb/
